summary: This document consists of email correspondence from September 2021 regarding a subpoena for testimony in the case United States v. Maxwell. The emails involve an FBI Special Agent, an Assistant United States Attorney, and an individual responding to the subpoena, discussing scheduling a follow-up conversation.

persons.name: Maurene Comey
persons.context: Assistant United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York corresponding about scheduling a call regarding a subpoena in the US v. Maxwell case.

events.title: Email exchange regarding subpoena follow-up
events.description: Email correspondence discussing scheduling a follow-up conversation regarding a subpoena to testify in US v. Maxwell.

events.title: Initial subpoena response coordination
events.description: Earlier email exchange where an individual responds to a subpoena in the US v. Maxwell case and an AUSA arranges to call them.

keyFacts: The emails discuss a subpoena for testimony in the criminal case United States v. Maxwell.
An FBI Special Agent from the New York Field Office's Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking unit is involved in the correspondence.
Assistant United States Attorney Maurene Comey of the Southern District of New York is coordinating a follow-up call regarding the subpoena.
An individual (name redacted) is responding to the subpoena and provides contact information.
The correspondence shows ongoing legal coordination in the Maxwell case as of September 2021.
